<p> </p>

<p>It was a brave, but deliberate ploy to distract Ambrose, who could scarcely believe what he had heard.  </p>

<p>'I was really upset with him and I told myself I'm going to make it damn hard for him. I'm really going to rough him up,' Ambrose said in 2016.</p>

<p>'I wasn't going to hurt him, but I was going to make him uncomfortable.'</p>

<p>Jones' career highlights are endless - standout moment include a shock World Cup win in 1987 followed by an Ashes triumph two years later over in England. </p>

<p>He finished up playing for Australia in 1994, and then forged a successful career in the media as a writer and commentator. </p>
